"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-07-26-paris-olympics-2024-opening-ceremony-parade-nations-order-explained-2-21302254\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The Parade of Nations for theParis2024Olympic Gamesopening ceremony has been confirmed, but how does it work and when do Great Britain enter?\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 141, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 121, \"end\": 134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9867171791484207, \"rank\": 0.01344268526281582, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics got underway in the French capital on Wednesday and continued on Thursday ahead of tonight's official opening ceremony on Friday, July 26, 2024.\", \"from\": 143, \"to\": 300, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 176, \"end\": 182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9622924165187843, \"rank\": 0.03912936548965014, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony will have a very different look this year with the event taking place on the River Seine with a special six-kilometre parade, the first time in history it has not taken place inside a stadium.\", \"from\": 302, \"to\": 515, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 400, \"end\": 411, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Around 600,000 people are expected to in attendance and many are anticipating it to be the largest opening ceremony in Olympic history.\", \"from\": 517, \"to\": 652, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The order of countries for any opening ceremony at the Olympics is\\u00a0decided alphabetically - using the host nation's official language - although there are a few exceptions, whichMetro.co.ukhas explained below.\", \"from\": 654, \"to\": 863, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At Tokyo 2020, nations entered according to their namesin the Japanese language, using the written form of katakana.\", \"from\": 865, \"to\": 981, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 927, \"end\": 944, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Japanese language\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\"}, {\"begin\": 972, \"end\": 980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katakana\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"katakana\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katakana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katakana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But what is the order for the Parade of Nations at Paris 2024 and how is it all decided?\", \"from\": 982, \"to\": 1070, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's everything you need to know ahead of tonight's historic event on the River Seine.\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1159, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1147, \"end\": 1158, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As many as 94 boats are expected to take part in the Paris Olympics opening ceremony river parade to carry an estimated amount of 6,800 athletes.\", \"from\": 1161, \"to\": 1306, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Parade of Nations will follow a six-kilometre (3.7 mile) course of the Seine, from east to west.\", \"from\": 1308, \"to\": 1408, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1383, \"end\": 1388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.466372483965304e-21, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Starting from Pont d'Austerlitz, it will come to a stop at the Pont d'I\\u00e9na before the opening ceremony's finale at the Trocad\\u00e9ro.\", \"from\": 1410, \"to\": 1539, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1424, \"end\": 1441, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'Austerlitz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pont d'Austerlitz\", \"types\": [\"Q12280\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'Austerlitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pont_d'Austerlitz\"}, {\"begin\": 1529, \"end\": 1538, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trocad\\u00e9ro\", \"score\": 0.9730907954876998, \"rank\": 0.023351147168026228, \"text\": \"Trocad\\u00e9ro\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trocad\\u00e9ro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trocad\\u00e9ro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the athletes sail, a show will unfurl around them.\", \"from\": 1541, \"to\": 1594, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There will be anumber of performances- withmusicians C\\u00e9line Dion and Lady Gagaexpected to appear.\", \"from\": 1595, \"to\": 1692, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1648, \"end\": 1659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"C\\u00e9line Dion\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Television broadcasts will begin at 6.30pm UK time, meaning you can watch the full spectacle from home.\", \"from\": 1694, \"to\": 1797, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1737, \"end\": 1739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999916559661649, \"rank\": 8.344038927439385e-06, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 planners wanted to make the opening ceremony more accessible to the wider public, which is why they decided to hold this one on the River Seine.\", \"from\": 1799, \"to\": 1954, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1799, \"end\": 1809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.808796865073153e-27, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1942, \"end\": 1953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first country to enter the Parade of Nations is alwaysGreece, due to their historical role in the origin of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1956, \"to\": 2081, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The very first ancient Olympic Games can be traced back to Olympia, in south west Greece, in 776 BC.\", \"from\": 2083, \"to\": 2183, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2142, \"end\": 2149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\", \"score\": 0.9999999997626219, \"rank\": 2.373339253081922e-10, \"text\": \"Olympia\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympia_London\"}, {\"begin\": 2160, \"end\": 2171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_Greece\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"west Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 2180, \"end\": 2182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anno_Domini\", \"score\": 0.9770163426046864, \"rank\": 0.023280204793520953, \"text\": \"BC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anno_Domini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anno_Domini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Greece will be followed by the Refugee Olympic Team.\", \"from\": 2184, \"to\": 2236, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2184, \"end\": 2190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9999904929192688, \"rank\": 9.340629868638597e-06, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 2215, \"end\": 2235, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999904503, \"rank\": 9.705867946565797e-12, \"text\": \"Refugee Olympic Team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IOC_Refugee_Olympic_Team_at_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Great Britain are 72nd on the list for the Parade of Nations, sandwiched in-between Ghana (71st) and Grenada (73rd).\", \"from\": 2238, \"to\": 2354, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2238, \"end\": 2251, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9867171791484207, \"rank\": 0.01344268526281582, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2322, \"end\": 2327, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ghana\", \"score\": 0.9989173755519634, \"rank\": 0.0010808034487863724, \"text\": \"Ghana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ghana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ghana\"}, {\"begin\": 2339, \"end\": 2346, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grenada\", \"score\": 0.9999954902961514, \"rank\": 3.296875563502383e-06, \"text\": \"Grenada\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grenada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grenada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The twoTeam GBflagbearers for Paris 2024 are diverTom Daleyand rower Helen Glover.\", \"from\": 2356, \"to\": 2438, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2425, \"end\": 2437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"score\": 0.9968858553495725, \"rank\": 0.0031234382808593376, \"text\": \"Helen Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Helen Glover and Tom Daley will carry the British flag at the Paris 2024 Opening Ceremony!\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2530, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2440, \"end\": 2452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"score\": 0.9968858553495725, \"rank\": 0.0031234382808593376, \"text\": \"Helen Glover\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Helen_Glover_(rower)\"}, {\"begin\": 2457, \"end\": 2466, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0685502772831799e-26, \"text\": \"Tom Daley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\"}, {\"begin\": 2482, \"end\": 2494, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Jack\", \"score\": 0.9648588276089732, \"rank\": 0.03637349283690275, \"text\": \"British flag\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Jack\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Union_Jack\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00ac\\u00f0\\u009f\\u0087\\u00a7@BritishRowing|@Aquatics_GBpic.twitter.com/c4Z7VGKeh1  'I am extremely proud,' Daley said.\", \"from\": 2531, \"to\": 2629, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'Being able to be flagbearer at the opening ceremony is a dream come true.'\", \"from\": 2630, \"to\": 2705, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Glover added: I never thought I would be an Olympian!\", \"from\": 2707, \"to\": 2760, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2751, \"end\": 2759, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9993251631095924, \"rank\": 0.000675273437299962, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Being part of history as a flagbearer, I have not really got my head round it yet.\", \"from\": 2761, \"to\": 2843, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Everyone I have told so far has cried, and I cried when I was told, which goes to show how much of an honour it is and how much it means.'\", \"from\": 2844, \"to\": 2982, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"France, this year's host nation, will enter last as the 205th country on the list, as per tradition.\", \"from\": 2984, \"to\": 3084, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2984, \"end\": 2990, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9997641693608574, \"rank\": 0.00016130094071836233, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The United States and Australia will come in as the 203rd and 204th nations, because they are hosting the next two Summer Olympics in 2028 and 2032.\", \"from\": 3086, \"to\": 3234, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3090, \"end\": 3103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999769911485, \"rank\": 1.564625817913006e-08, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3108, \"end\": 3117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"score\": 0.999973372753438, \"rank\": 2.0895247233983587e-05, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Los Angeles is the host city for the next Games while the first Olympics of the 2030s will take place in Brisbane.\", \"from\": 3236, \"to\": 3350, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3236, \"end\": 3247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999987359232168, \"rank\": 1.259870973995265e-06, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 3341, \"end\": 3349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\", \"score\": 0.9990890691295844, \"rank\": 0.0009115651448368238, \"text\": \"Brisbane\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ArrowMORE:British Olympic chief slams decision to allow Dutch rapist to compete  ArrowMORE:Team GB hire their own chefs after being served raw meat in Olympic Village  ArrowMORE:Trains filled with Olympic athletes stopped after coordinated arson attacks  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.\", \"from\": 3352, \"to\": 3717, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3362, \"end\": 3369, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999901688421552, \"rank\": 3.853883905219834e-06, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http: